Package: RobustBCCGRegression
Title: Robust Regression for the Box-Cox Cole and Green Distribution via MDPDE
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Arthur", "Gonçalves de Souza", , "arthurgo.souza@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Implements robust estimation of Box-Cox Cole and Green (BCCG) regression
    models using the Minimum Density Power Divergence Estimator (MDPDE), as proposed
    by Basu et al. (1998) <doi:10.1093/biomet/85.3.549>. The BCCG distribution, 
    introduced by Cole and Green (1992), models strictly positive, potentially skewed
    responses via three parameters: median (mu), approximate coefficient of variation
    (sigma), and skewness (nu). The package provides MDPDE-based estimation that
    downweights outliers, an automatic data-driven alpha selection procedure via
    trimmed negative log-likelihood (LVNMP), sandwich-based asymptotic covariance
    estimation, and diagnostic tools including quantile residuals, worm plots, and
    a weights-versus-residuals plot. The MLE special case (alpha = 0) is handled
    via the 'gamlss' package.
